{"title_page": "25TFM-NBOMe", "text_new": "{{Drugbox\n| Verifiedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 451564986\n| IUPAC_name = 2-(4-trifluoromethyl-2,5-dimethoxyphenyl)-''N''-[(2-methoxyphenyl)methyl]ethanamine\n| image = 2C-TFM-NBOMe.svg\n| width = 200\n\n<!--Clinical data-->\n| tradename =  \n\n<!--Identifiers-->\n| CAS_number_Ref = {{cascite|correct|CAS}}\n| CAS_number = 1027161-33-6\n| UNII_Ref = {{fdacite|correct|FDA}}\n| UNII = X3V8LI2TUV \n| PubChem = 10067667\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 8243207\n\n<!--Chemical data-->\n| C=19 | H=22 | F=3 | N=1 | O=3 \n| molecular_weight = 369.377 g/mol\n| smiles = FC(F)(F)c1c(OC)cc(c(OC)c1)CCNCc2ccccc2OC\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI = 1S/C19H22F3NO3/c1-24-16-7-5-4-6-14(16)12-23-9-8-13-10-18(26-3)15(19(20,21)22)11-17(13)25-2/h4-7,10-11,23H,8-9,12H2,1-3H3\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = FBHVTQIAHOTPAM-UHFFFAOYSA-N\n}}\n\n'''25TFM-NBOMe''' (also known as '''NBOMe-2C-TFM''', '''2C-TFM-NBOMe''', and '''Cimbi-138''') is a derivative of the [[phenethylamine]] [[Psychedelic drug|hallucinogen]] [[2C-TFM]], discovered in 2004 by Ralf Heim at the [[Free University of Berlin]].<ref>[http://www.diss.fu-berlin.de/diss/receive/FUDISS_thesis_000000001221 Ralf Heim PhD. Synthese und Pharmakologie potenter 5-HT2A-Rezeptoragonisten mit N-2-Methoxybenzyl-Partialstruktur. Entwicklung eines neuen Struktur-Wirkungskonzepts. (German)]</ref> It acts as a potent [[partial agonist]] for the [[5HT2A receptor|5HT<sub>2A</sub>]] [[Receptor (biochemistry)|receptor]], though its relative potency is disputed, with some studies finding it to be of lower potency than [[25I-NBOMe]],<ref>[http://epub.uni-regensburg.de/12119/ Maria Silva PhD. Theoretical study of the interaction of agonists with the 5-HT2A receptor. Universit\u00e4t Regensburg, 2009.]</ref><ref name=\"pmid21088982\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Silva ME, Heim R, Strasser A, Elz S, Dove S |title=Theoretical studies on the interaction of partial agonists with the 5-HT(2A) receptor |journal=Journal of Computer-aided Molecular Design |volume=25 |issue=1 |pages=51\u201366 |date=January 2011 |pmid=21088982 |doi=10.1007/s10822-010-9400-2 |url=|citeseerx=10.1.1.688.2670 }}</ref>  while others show it to be of similar or higher potency,<ref>{{Cite journal |doi= 10.1007/s00259-010-1686-8 |last= Ettrup |first= A. | last2= Hansen | first2= M. |last3= Santini | first3= M. A. |last4= Paine | first4= J. |last5= Gillings | first5= N. |last6= Palner | first6= M. |last7= Lehel | first7= S. |last8= Herth | first8= M. M. |last9= Madsen | first9= J. | first10= J. | last10= Kristensen |displayauthors=9 | first11= M. | last11 = Begtrup | first12= G. M. | last12 = Knudsen | title = Radiosynthesis and ''in vivo'' evaluation of a series of substituted <sup>11</sup>C-phenethylamines as 5-HT<sub>2A</sub> agonist PET tracers |journal= European Journal of Nuclear Medicine and Molecular Imaging |volume= 38 |issue= 4 |pages= 681\u201393 |year= 2010 |pmid= 21174090 }}\n</ref> possibly because of differences in the assay used.<ref>{{cite thesis | vauthors = Hansen M | title = Design and Synthesis of Selective Serotonin Receptor Agonists for Positron Emission Tomography Imaging of the Brain. | degree = Ph.D. | publisher = University of Copenhagen | date = 2010-12-16 | doi = 10.13140/RG.2.2.33671.14245}}</ref> 2C-TFM-NB2OMe can be taken to produce psychedelic effects similar to 2C-I-NB2OMe and 2C-D-NB2OMe.\n\n==Legality==\n\n===United Kingdom===\n{{N-benzylphenethylamine-Legality-United Kingdom}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[DOTFM]]\n* [[TFMFly]]\n* [[2CBCB-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-TCB-2)\n* [[2CBFly-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CB-Fly)\n* [[25C-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CC)\n* [[25B-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CB)\n* [[25D-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CD)\n* [[25I-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CI)\n* [[25I-NBMD]] (NBMD-2CI)\n* [[25B-NBOH]]\n* [[25I-NBOH]] (NBOH-2CI)\n* [[25I-NBF]] (NBF-2CI)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hallucinogens}}\n{{Serotonin receptor modulators}}\n{{Phenethylamines}}\n\n[[Category:25-NB (psychedelics)]]\n[[Category:Trifluoromethyl compounds]]\n\n{{hallucinogen-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Drugbox\n| Verifiedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 451564986\n| IUPAC_name = 2-(4-trifluoromethyl-2,5-dimethoxyphenyl)-''N''-[(2-methoxyphenyl)methyl]ethanamine\n| image = 2C-TFM-NBOMe.svg\n| width = 200\n\n<!--Clinical data-->\n| tradename =  \n\n<!--Identifiers-->\n| CAS_number_Ref = {{cascite|changed|??}}\n| CAS_number = 1027161-33-6 \n| PubChem = 10067667\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 8243207\n\n<!--Chemical data-->\n| C=19 | H=22 | F=3 | N=1 | O=3 \n| molecular_weight = 369.377 g/mol\n| smiles = FC(F)(F)c1c(OC)cc(c(OC)c1)CCNCc2ccccc2OC\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI = 1S/C19H22F3NO3/c1-24-16-7-5-4-6-14(16)12-23-9-8-13-10-18(26-3)15(19(20,21)22)11-17(13)25-2/h4-7,10-11,23H,8-9,12H2,1-3H3\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = FBHVTQIAHOTPAM-UHFFFAOYSA-N\n}}\n\n'''25TFM-NBOMe''' (also known as '''NBOMe-2C-TFM''', '''2C-TFM-NBOMe''', and '''Cimbi-138''') is a derivative of the [[phenethylamine]] [[Psychedelic drug|hallucinogen]] [[2C-TFM]], discovered in 2004 by Ralf Heim at the [[Free University of Berlin]].<ref>[http://www.diss.fu-berlin.de/diss/receive/FUDISS_thesis_000000001221 Ralf Heim PhD. Synthese und Pharmakologie potenter 5-HT2A-Rezeptoragonisten mit N-2-Methoxybenzyl-Partialstruktur. Entwicklung eines neuen Struktur-Wirkungskonzepts. (German)]</ref> It acts as a potent [[partial agonist]] for the [[5HT2A receptor|5HT<sub>2A</sub>]] [[Receptor (biochemistry)|receptor]], though its relative potency is disputed, with some studies finding it to be of lower potency than [[25I-NBOMe]],<ref>[http://epub.uni-regensburg.de/12119/ Maria Silva PhD. Theoretical study of the interaction of agonists with the 5-HT2A receptor. Universit\u00e4t Regensburg, 2009.]</ref><ref name=\"pmid21088982\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Silva ME, Heim R, Strasser A, Elz S, Dove S |title=Theoretical studies on the interaction of partial agonists with the 5-HT(2A) receptor |journal=Journal of Computer-aided Molecular Design |volume=25 |issue=1 |pages=51\u201366 |date=January 2011 |pmid=21088982 |doi=10.1007/s10822-010-9400-2 |url=|citeseerx=10.1.1.688.2670 }}</ref>  while others show it to be of similar or higher potency,<ref>{{Cite journal |doi= 10.1007/s00259-010-1686-8 |last= Ettrup |first= A. | last2= Hansen | first2= M. |last3= Santini | first3= M. A. |last4= Paine | first4= J. |last5= Gillings | first5= N. |last6= Palner | first6= M. |last7= Lehel | first7= S. |last8= Herth | first8= M. M. |last9= Madsen | first9= J. | first10= J. | last10= Kristensen |displayauthors=9 | first11= M. | last11 = Begtrup | first12= G. M. | last12 = Knudsen | title = Radiosynthesis and ''in vivo'' evaluation of a series of substituted <sup>11</sup>C-phenethylamines as 5-HT<sub>2A</sub> agonist PET tracers |journal= European Journal of Nuclear Medicine and Molecular Imaging |volume= 38 |issue= 4 |pages= 681\u201393 |year= 2010 |pmid= 21174090 }}\n</ref> possibly because of differences in the assay used.<ref>{{cite thesis | vauthors = Hansen M | title = Design and Synthesis of Selective Serotonin Receptor Agonists for Positron Emission Tomography Imaging of the Brain. | degree = Ph.D. | publisher = University of Copenhagen | date = 2010-12-16 | doi = 10.13140/RG.2.2.33671.14245}}</ref> 2C-TFM-NB2OMe can be taken to produce psychedelic effects similar to 2C-I-NB2OMe and 2C-D-NB2OMe.\n\n==Legality==\n\n===United Kingdom===\n{{N-benzylphenethylamine-Legality-United Kingdom}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[DOTFM]]\n* [[TFMFly]]\n* [[2CBCB-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-TCB-2)\n* [[2CBFly-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CB-Fly)\n* [[25C-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CC)\n* [[25B-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CB)\n* [[25D-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CD)\n* [[25I-NBOMe]] (NBOMe-2CI)\n* [[25I-NBMD]] (NBMD-2CI)\n* [[25B-NBOH]]\n* [[25I-NBOH]] (NBOH-2CI)\n* [[25I-NBF]